ot trying to enter US territory. However, this man was detained under suspicion of being an Al-Quaeda terrorist (all evidence currently available indicates that he isn't, but he's been found guilty by birthright for being Syrian and knowing somebody who had an alleged contact with that organization over a year ago), and was deported to Syria. He disappeared 10 days ago, and nobody knows where he is, if he's even still alive.<br>
<br>
What I find most interesting about this is that American media isn't covering it at all. Most Americans don't even know about it, nor have they ever heard the name <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Maher Arar</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. To pour salt into an open wound, your ambassador smirked to himself, and said that maybe we should ask our internal people where he is, and stop bothering theirs. 200 years of friendly relations with our country, and your &quot;ambassador&quot; is willing to dissolve it because this man was a 3rd hop in a train of alleged associations. Has your leadership completely lost touch with reality? <br>
<br>
<br>
I encourage those among you living in the states to write to your leaders. At the least, have that dickhead you call an ambassador recalled, and ideally return the innocent Canadian citizen back to his home. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uatro.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atro</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/19/02 11:01:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1722.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Americans enforcing internal laws in international terri</span><hr size=1> After reading that article he doesn't sound too innocent to me. He was wanted for a crime in his home country, didn't register as an islamic immigrant, and had a terrorist contact in his past. Personally I'm glad he was deported. Sounds like there was more involved that just the info that article had anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/uaurianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurianne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mana Whore</span><br>  Posts: 1346<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(10/19/02 12:09:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1722.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Americans enforcing internal laws in international terri</span><hr size=1> Actually, sparky, he wasn't wanted in Canada. We don't need to register in Canada as an immigrant from an islamic nation, and the &quot;tie&quot; to a terrorist organi